results.name: a(1) = 1; for n > 1, a(n) = A255127(A260738(n)+1, A260739(n)).
comment: a(n) = the number located immediately below n in A255127 (square array generated by Ludic sieve) in the same column where n itself is, or in other words, the number removed in the next filtering stage at the same step as when n was removed in the A260738(n)-th stage.
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..32999
program: (Scheme) (define (A269379 n) (if (= 1 n) n (A255127bi (+ (A260738 n) 1) (A260739 n)))) ;; Code for A255127bi given in A255127.
xref: Cf. A269171, A269356, A269358, A269382, A269385, A269387 (sequences that use this function).
